description: This file is a minified JavaScript library, specifically the minified version of vis.js version 4.17.0, a dynamic browser-based visualization library. It provides visualization components like network graphs, data sets, and utilities for creating and managing visualizations in web applications.

classes.name: Node
classes.description: Represents a node in the network graph, encapsulating properties like position, size, shape, label, and linked edges.

classes.name: Edge
classes.description: Represents an edge in the network graph connecting nodes, with properties for styling, labels, and shape.

classes.name: Network
classes.description: Main class for handling network visualization, managing nodes, edges, layout, physics, and user interactions.

methods.name: setOptions
methods.description: Configures the network with provided options, updating layout, physics, interaction, and rendering settings.

methods.name: setData
methods.description: Loads nodes and edges data into the network, initializing or updating the visualization.

methods.name: draw
methods.description: Renders the network visualization on the canvas.

methods.name: moveNode
methods.description: Programmatically moves a node to specified coordinates.

methods.name: getConnectedNodes
methods.description: Returns a list of nodes connected to a specified node.

methods.name: getConnectedEdges
methods.description: Returns edges connected to a specified node.

methods.name: addNode
methods.description: Adds a new node to the network.

methods.name: addEdge
methods.description: Adds a new edge to the network.

methods.name: removeNode
methods.description: Removes a node from the network.

methods.name: removeEdge
methods.description: Removes an edge from the network.
